# bittorrent-tracker is the standalone server + client library that powers
# every WebTorrent project (instant.io, webtorrent-desktop, webtorrent
# CLI).  Runs three trackers in one process by default: HTTP (BEP 0003
# standard tracker protocol), UDP (BEP 0015 — UDP tracker protocol), and
# WebSocket (BEP-INVALID-but-everyone-implements-it WebRTC tracker for
# browser peers).  Browser peers receive WebRTC offer/answer SDPs via the
# WS tracker, then connect peer-to-peer over RTCPeerConnection using
# `@thaunknown/simple-peer`.  Standalone runtime stats served on the
# same HTTP port at `/stats` (JSON) and `/stats.json` (machine-readable).
#
